would last just a couple of years.

00:08:20.090 --> 00:08:23.441
This year marks my 25th anniversary.

00:08:23.441 --> 00:08:28.357
Even after trying to move to
Toronto to be closer to my

00:08:28.357 --> 00:08:33.499
family in 2006,
CMU exerted its magnetic pull and

00:08:33.499 --> 00:08:37.880
drew our family back
after a brief six months.

00:08:40.220 --> 00:08:45.255
I've served under three
previous presidents at CMU

00:08:45.260 --> 00:08:49.160
and am delighted to join you
in welcoming the University's

00:08:49.160 --> 00:08:53.540
tenth President, Dr. Farnam Jahanian.

00:08:53.540 --> 00:09:02.080
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]

00:09:02.080 --> 00:09:07.140
&gt;&gt; I also take much pleasure in welcoming Dr. Jahanian's wife, Tris,

00:09:07.160 --> 00:09:11.834
whom I have come to know
over these past few years,

00:09:11.834 --> 00:09:15.937
as well as all the members
of the Jahanian family.

00:09:15.937 --> 00:09:24.357
&gt;&gt; [APPLAUSE]

00:09:24.360 --> 00:09:27.000
&gt;&gt; I am truly honored to have been

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:31.460
chosen as a speaker for
this august ceremony and

00:09:31.460 --> 00:09:35.720
am unreservedly supportive of Dr.
Jahanian.

00:09:37.160 --> 00:09:42.590
I have witnessed him close up in
action over the last four years and

00:09:42.590 --> 00:09:45.851
have observed his gracious behavior,

00:09:45.851 --> 00:09:50.806
even on those occasions when
I've been a thorn in his side.

00:09:53.567 --> 00:09:58.508
Particularly remarkable is that Dr.
Jahanian takes time

00:09:58.508 --> 00:10:03.560
to listen to the multiple
constituencies that make up CMU.

00:10:05.330 --> 00:10:10.750
I served as a co-chair of the task force
to enhance the students' experience.

00:10:11.900 --> 00:10:18.510
As provost, he not only initiated this
task force, but he remains supportive and

00:10:18.510 --> 00:10:24.970
involved in its work even when
he was no longer provost.

00:10:24.970 --> 00:10:29.983
Stepping back,
I am struck by how CMU has evolved

00:10:29.983 --> 00:10:34.762
since my first year here way back in 1993.

00:10:34.762 --> 00:10:38.682
It is truly staggering.

00:10:38.682 --> 00:10:43.137
Some of this evolution is
a result of the expansion and

00:10:43.137 --> 00:10:47.295
growth of the physical
setting of the campus and

00:10:47.295 --> 00:10:54.430
the recruitment of outstanding new
faculty, staff and importantly, students.

00:10:56.230 --> 00:11:03.900
But this evolution is reaping the benefits
of hard work done over generations

00:11:03.900 --> 00:11:08.380
to build CMU as an educational and
research powerhouse.

00:11:10.260 --> 00:11:14.402
And as links in the chain
of this ongoing community,

00:11:14.402 --> 00:11:21.440
we have all forged a common bond
with a perpetual commitment

00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:28.080
to improve the students' experience,
to enhance the educational opportunities,

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:33.860
to engage our alumni and
to conduct cutting edge research

00:11:34.890 --> 00:11:39.110
that makes a difference to our society and
our world.

00:11:41.130 --> 00:11:44.930
I'd like to share with you a comment
made to me a couple of weeks ago.

00:11:44.930 --> 00:11:49.112
I was having lunch with a junior in
mechanical engineering, Alex Markowitz,

00:11:49.112 --> 00:11:55.680
and in discussing CMU, he said,
it just does not get better than this.

00:11:57.090 --> 00:11:57.910
And he is right.

00:11:59.280 --> 00:12:03.320
My personal commitment to
the institution is clear, too.

00:12:04.750 --> 00:12:08.950
My husband, David Plaut,
who is also a faculty member here, and

00:12:08.950 --> 00:12:14.470
I, have entrusted CMU with
the education of our own children.

00:12:16.030 --> 00:12:18.340
It just does not get better than this.

00:12:19.360 --> 00:12:21.970
We're a CMU family through and through.

00:12:24.090 --> 00:12:29.260
And so, as we begin this new
chapter in the evolving

00:12:29.260 --> 00:12:35.180
book of Carnegie Mellon University,
my colleagues and I dedicate ourselves

00:12:35.180 --> 00:12:40.430
to continue building an institution
of the very highest caliber

00:12:42.090 --> 00:12:47.162
with a commitment to an inclusive and
equitable campus for

00:12:47.162 --> 00:12:51.095
all of its members and
with opportunities for

00:12:51.095 --> 00:12:56.286
all to realize their educational and
research potential.

00:12:56.286 --> 00:13:00.198
Dr. Jahanian has clearly expressed his

00:13:00.198 --> 00:13:05.031
commitment to facilitating
these initiatives

00:13:05.031 --> 00:13:09.642
and we are all so
excited to see what comes next.

00:13:09.642 --> 00:13:10.682
Thank you.

