And this is where we have the convergence,
the perfect storm of social, and mobile,

00:20:46.630 --> 00:20:49.754
and deep learning, and artificial
intelligence, and 3D printing, and

00:20:49.754 --> 00:20:54.640
amazing technologies all brought
together to drive incredible innovation.

00:20:56.010 --> 00:20:59.330
Now, like many of you,
I have the opportunity and

00:20:59.330 --> 00:21:02.170
good fortune to speak with other CEOs and
world leaders.

00:21:02.170 --> 00:21:04.970
And what is top of mind in that group

00:21:06.170 --> 00:21:09.790
is how to harness this wave of
innovation in a very positive way.

00:21:10.800 --> 00:21:14.970
This convergence of technology is
having a profound impact on our world.

00:21:14.970 --> 00:21:16.379
We see it in our daily lives.

00:21:17.620 --> 00:21:21.900
It has also brought great disruption and
given rise to many, many questions.

00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:25.350
What will these new technologies be?

00:21:25.350 --> 00:21:27.700
Will they be positive for mankind?

00:21:27.700 --> 00:21:30.130
What are the socioeconomic effects?

00:21:30.130 --> 00:21:32.347
What are the privacy implications?

00:21:32.347 --> 00:21:34.679
What will be the regulatory issues?

00:21:34.680 --> 00:21:36.320
What will be the future of work?

00:21:37.760 --> 00:21:42.200
And Farnam is passionate about these
questions and even more passionate

00:21:42.320 --> 00:21:47.040
about CMU leading the way to drive
those answers to these questions.

00:21:47.040 --> 00:21:52.020
These are all important issues of our time
that we have to consider in a thoughtful,

00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:53.400
and meaningful, and measured way.

00:21:54.820 --> 00:21:56.780
We are clearly at an inflection point.

00:21:57.800 --> 00:22:01.610
These advances must be for good.

00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:03.690
They must enlighten, they must empower,

00:22:03.690 --> 00:22:06.200
and they must take humanity
to greater heights

00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:10.230
and in a world where there is
an ever increasing divide,

00:22:10.230 --> 00:22:15.118
these advances must create opportunity for
all, not just a few, so

00:22:15.118 --> 00:22:19.009
that all of mankind can participate and
contribute.

00:22:19.009 --> 00:22:20.403
Now, this will take vigilance.

00:22:20.403 --> 00:22:23.840
It will take dedication and
it will take leadership.

00:22:23.840 --> 00:22:26.410
And this is why the faculty,
the staff, the students,

00:22:26.410 --> 00:22:30.376
this community at Carnegie Mellon are so
critical to the future of this nation,

00:22:30.376 --> 00:22:35.140
this society, this world.

00:22:35.140 --> 00:22:38.620
For the young minds that we shape
here have an important mission.

00:22:38.620 --> 00:22:40.910
They will go forth into the world
with the knowledge, the vision, and

00:22:40.910 --> 00:22:43.390
the ethics that Carnegie Mellon
has instilled in them.

00:22:43.390 --> 00:22:46.710
And they will go forward into the world

00:22:46.710 --> 00:22:51.720
to solve universal issues that lie at the
intersection of technology and humanity.

00:22:53.100 --> 00:22:57.040
The graduates of CMU must be equipped to
thrive and lead in a world of uncertainty.

00:22:57.040 --> 00:22:59.110
For these are truly uncertain times.

00:23:00.320 --> 00:23:03.830
Today, the value of trust is
being questioned more than ever.

00:23:04.850 --> 00:23:09.940
Trust in technology, trust in our
institutions, trust in our leaders.

00:23:09.940 --> 00:23:11.814
Some would say there is a crisis of trust

00:23:13.737 --> 00:23:16.599
and this crisis of trust has
created a leadership void.

00:23:17.600 --> 00:23:20.675
And now individuals, and
companies, and faculty, and

00:23:20.675 --> 00:23:22.797
students alike must fill this breach

00:23:22.797 --> 00:23:26.330
and it will be the graduates of CMU that
will answer this call for leadership

00:23:26.330 --> 00:23:28.100
and for them, it is a call to arms.

00:23:28.100 --> 00:23:30.060
It is a call to arms for us all.

00:23:30.060 --> 00:23:33.480
It is an obligation to
lead in an ethical and

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:39.120
transparent way,
to engage in constructive civil discourse,

00:23:39.120 --> 00:23:42.920
where disagreements will arise
and that's okay, but

00:23:42.920 --> 00:23:45.330
dialogue must happen with respect,

00:23:45.330 --> 00:23:48.520
and while there can be differing opinions,
there cannot be differing facts,

00:23:49.560 --> 00:23:53.160
and, most important, most important,

00:23:53.160 --> 00:23:57.080
to restore trust in our society,
because without trust, we have nothing.

00:23:58.980 --> 00:24:01.500
It will be the graduates of Carnegie
Mellon that will be called upon to

00:24:01.500 --> 00:24:04.950
cultivate and drive a culture of
success in business and society,

00:24:04.950 --> 00:24:09.936
where the core tenants of diversity, empathy, equality, humanity,

00:24:09.936 --> 00:24:14.900
accountability, and opportunity for
all are at the forefront.

00:24:16.580 --> 00:24:20.600
Never before has this institution
been more important to the world.

00:24:20.600 --> 00:24:24.480
Never before has leadership at the
intersection of technology, and society

00:24:24.480 --> 00:24:27.440
and humanity been as
critical as it is right now.

00:24:27.440 --> 00:24:32.390
And though the future is unwritten I
am very confident, very confident that

00:24:32.390 --> 00:24:35.350
the graduates at CMU will be the authors
of a great future for all of us.

00:24:37.590 --> 00:24:40.190
Now, as we stand at
the doorstep of this new world,

00:24:40.190 --> 00:24:44.100
the dawn of a new era,
we need a truly special leader.

00:24:44.100 --> 00:24:44.720
To help guide and

00:24:44.720 --> 00:24:48.900
shape the lives of those who will
determine the future, all of our futures

00:24:48.900 --> 00:24:51.830
and never before has a presidency
of this institution been

00:24:51.830 --> 00:24:53.240
as important as it is right now

00:24:54.530 --> 00:24:58.940
and it requires a remarkable leader,
a truly outstanding human being, and

00:24:58.940 --> 00:25:01.790
that person is Dr. Farnam Jahanian.

00:25:01.790 --> 00:25:03.110
We stand with Farnam today,

00:25:03.110 --> 00:25:06.770
as he takes his rightful place amongst
the great presidents of Carnegie Mellon.

00:25:07.880 --> 00:25:12.950
I cannot imagine a better leader
who embodies the values of CMU.

00:25:12.950 --> 00:25:18.628
I cannot imagine a better leader with
as much vision, with as much passion,

00:25:18.628 --> 00:25:19.630
with as much focus

00:25:19.630 --> 00:25:22.940
and I cannot imagine a better leader and
torch-bearer of this great institution.

00:25:24.470 --> 00:25:27.640
Farnam, we are very lucky to have you.

00:25:27.640 --> 00:25:30.159
You are the right leader,
