but there's an historical

00:34:43.450 --> 00:34:47.560
connection between Carnegie Mellon and
my own university, Cornell.

00:34:47.560 --> 00:34:53.810
Andrew Carnegie was one of Cornell's first
trustees, elected to that role in 1890.

00:34:53.810 --> 00:34:59.350
Later, honoring his passion for music,
Carnegie donated to Cornell a magnificent

00:34:59.350 --> 00:35:04.090
organ to celebrate the 80th birthday of
our first president, Andrew Dixon White.

00:35:05.095 --> 00:35:08.710
Alas, the organ suffered a ignoble fate.

00:35:08.710 --> 00:35:13.720
It's air intake, for some inexplicable
reason, was located in the men's bathroom,

00:35:15.730 --> 00:35:21.300
and in 1935 there was a plumbing failure
that filled that room with water.

00:35:21.300 --> 00:35:25.340
Unaware of this, the university
organist sat down at the instrument and

00:35:25.340 --> 00:35:29.553
according to historical account,
blew a mighty crescendo,

00:35:29.553 --> 00:35:33.285
which filled the leather organ
pouches with water, ruining them.

00:35:33.285 --> 00:35:36.590
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Perhaps we're doing better off with

00:35:36.590 --> 00:35:37.805
a gift of bag pipes.

00:35:37.805 --> 00:35:40.430
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]
&gt;&gt; Now,

00:35:40.430 --> 00:35:43.070
there is also a long time
connection between Farnam and me,

00:35:43.070 --> 00:35:46.460
although of course not as long
as between our universities.

00:35:46.460 --> 00:35:50.880
As Rebecca said, Farnam and I met about
20 years ago when we were both faculty

00:35:50.880 --> 00:35:55.130
members in computer science and
engineering at the University of Michigan.

00:35:55.130 --> 00:35:59.450
I later became Chair of CSE and
Farnam succeeded me in that role.

00:35:59.450 --> 00:36:02.420
Later, he became provost
here at Carnegie Mellon,

00:36:02.420 --> 00:36:05.540
a few years after I had
become provost at Michigan.

00:36:05.540 --> 00:36:07.830
And he started as interim president here,

00:36:07.830 --> 00:36:11.118
just a couple of months after
I became Cornell's president.

00:36:11.118 --> 00:36:19.365
&gt;&gt; [LAUGH]

