you're the president of a university.

00:36:50.560 --> 00:36:55.230
But really, having everything be
your fault is a fair trade off for

00:36:55.230 --> 00:36:58.960
all that is wonderful about
being a university president.

00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:03.805
It is, as I know Farnham appreciates,
a huge privilege to lead a university,

00:37:03.805 --> 00:37:07.130
especially a great one
like Carnegie Mellon.

00:37:07.130 --> 00:37:11.416
Universities are institutions that
are second to none in changing lives.

00:37:11.416 --> 00:37:13.938
We change the lives of our students.

00:37:13.938 --> 00:37:18.830
We change the lives of the communities
into which our students graduate

00:37:18.830 --> 00:37:23.140
and we changed the lives of all those
who are touched by the research and

00:37:23.140 --> 00:37:25.800
the scholarship of our faculty.

00:37:25.800 --> 00:37:30.770
Farnam, I can assure you is the perfect
choice to lead Carnegie Mellon and

00:37:30.770 --> 00:37:34.890
to ensure that it continues it's
proud tradition of changing lives for

00:37:34.890 --> 00:37:36.290
the better.

